Re: Topic marker in context of passive sentence
by JaySee » Fri 01.22.2010 2:07 am It's not at all uncommon to see 'wo' used in passive sentences. It turns the sentence into a 迷惑の受け身 (meiwaku no ukemi), and is used in contexts associated with negative feelings.私は雨に降られた私は泥棒に財布を盗まれたetc. I'm not a native speaker, but I don't particularly see anything wrong with 私は弟にカメラを壊されました.
JaySee
