Re: Topic marker in context of passive sentence
by pm215 » Fri 01.22.2010 5:27 am pbj005 wrote:I would like to know when to use wa and when to use ga ?Wouldn't we all? I believe (though I might be wrong) that the choice of wa/ga is governed by the same kind of things as it is for an active sentence -- passive sentences aren't particularly 'special' here.雨が降られて、服がぬれてしまいました。I was kind of expecting this to be 雨に but google certainly has a reasonable number of hits for 雨が降られて...
